Manufacturing Pack Telemetry Collector and Downtime Alerts
Prerequisites
Basic Linux command line knowledge
Understanding of system processes and services
Familiarity with Python programming
Basic networking concepts (HTTP, ports)
Text editor experience (vim, nano, or similar)
Learning Objectives
By completing this lab, you will:

Implement a telemetry collection system for manufacturing equipment
Build downtime detection logic using threshold monitoring
Configure alert mechanisms for production system failures
Deploy a monitoring solution using open-source tools
Environment Setup
You will use the bare-metal Linux machine provided through the "Start Lab" button. All tools will be installed during this lab.

Install Required Packages
# Update package manager
sudo apt update

# Install Python and pip
sudo apt install -y python3 python3-pip python3-venv

# Install InfluxDB (time-series database for telemetry)
wget -q https://repos.influxdata.com/influxdata-archive_compat.key
echo '393e8779c89ac8d958f81f942f9ad7fb82a25e133faddaf92e15b16e6ac9ce4c influxdata-archive_compat.key' | sha256sum -c && cat influxdata-archive_compat.key | gpg --dearmor | sudo tee /etc/apt/trusted.gpg.d/influxdata-archive_compat.gpg > /dev/null
echo 'deb [signed-by=/etc/apt/trusted.gpg.d/influxdata-archive_compat.gpg] https://repos.influxdata.com/debian stable main' | sudo tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/influxdata.list
sudo apt update && sudo apt install -y influxdb

# Install Telegraf (telemetry collector)
sudo apt install -y telegraf

# Start InfluxDB
sudo systemctl start influxdb
sudo systemctl enable influxdb
Create Python Virtual Environment
# Create project directory
mkdir -p ~/manufacturing-monitor
cd ~/manufacturing-monitor

# Create virtual environment
python3 -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate

# Install Python dependencies
pip install influxdb-client requests
