Troubleshooting Tips
InfluxDB Connection Errors:

# Check if InfluxDB is running
sudo systemctl status influxdb

# Restart if needed
sudo systemctl restart influxdb

# Verify port is listening
netstat -tlnp | grep 8086
No Data in Database:

Verify simulator is running without errors
Check Python virtual environment is activated
Confirm database name matches in both scripts
Alerts Not Triggering:

Verify downtime threshold settings
Check query time windows are appropriate
Ensure equipment IDs match between simulator and monitor
Python Import Errors:

# Reinstall dependencies
pip install --upgrade influxdb-client requests
Conclusion
You have successfully built a manufacturing telemetry collection and downtime alert system using open-source tools. This lab demonstrated:

Real-time telemetry collection from production equipment
Time-series data storage and querying with InfluxDB
Automated downtime detection using threshold monitoring
Alert generation for production system failures
This architecture is used in real manufacturing environments to minimize downtime, improve equipment utilization, and enable predictive maintenance. The skills learned apply directly to DevOps roles in industrial IoT, manufacturing operations, and production monitoring systems.

